					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Sarah Montague</h4>
												<p>Sarah Montague is an award-winning veteran radio, audio and podcast producer of drama, documentary and features, whose work (with WNYC, NPR, PRX, and other outlets) includes Audio Maverick, a documentary podcast about the life and times of Golden Age radio producer Himan Brown, and radio and audio theater series including Jazzplay; The Radio Stage; T is for Tom; Spinning Stoppard; and the plays The Fall of the City; Anesthesia and That Deep Ocean.</p>
					</div>
